  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some greatest operations by Ajit Doval?",
  "response": "Ajit Doval, the current National Security Advisor (NSA) of India, is renowned for his strategic acumen and operational expertise in the realm of national security and intelligence. Over his illustrious career, both in the Indian Police Service (IPS) and as a key figure in India's intelligence apparatus, he has been involved in several high-profile operations and strategic initiatives. Here are some notable highlights:\n\n### 1. **Operation Blue Star (1984)**  \n   - Ajit Doval played a pivotal role in the lead-up to Operation Blue Star, during which he infiltrated the Golden Temple in Amritsar posing as a Pakistani intelligence agent. His intelligence gathering provided critical insights to the Indian government about the militant activities inside the temple.\n\n### 2. **Mizoram Peace Accord (1986)**  \n   - Doval was instrumental in negotiating the Mizoram Peace Accord, which ended decades of insurgency in the northeastern state of Mizoram and brought stability to the region.\n\n### 3. **Counter-Terrorism Operations in Kashmir**  \n   - As an intelligence operative, Doval was deeply involved in counter-terrorism efforts in Jammu and Kashmir, including neutralizing several militant groups and orchestrating the surrender of numerous militants.\n\n### 4. **Kandahar Hijacking (1999)**  \n   - During the hijacking of Indian Airlines Flight IC-814 by Pakistani terrorists, Doval was part of the crisis management team and advocated for a strong, non-compromising stance.\n\n### 5. **Naga Peace Talks**  \n   - Doval has played a key role in facilitating peace negotiations with Naga insurgent groups, aiming to bring a lasting resolution to the decades-old conflict in Nagaland.\n\n### 6. **Surgical Strikes (2016)**  \n   - As NSA, Doval was a key architect of the 2016 surgical strikes across the Line of Control (LoC) in response to the Uri terror attack. This bold operation demonstrated India\u2019s resolve to retaliate against cross-border terrorism.\n\n### 7. **Balakot Airstrike (2019)**  \n   - Doval was a central figure in planning and executing the Balakot airstrike in response to the Pulwama terror attack. This operation targeted a Jaish-e-Mohammed (JeM) training camp in Pakistan and marked a significant escalation in India\u2019s counter-terrorism strategy.\n\n### 8. **Abrogation of Article 370 (2019)**  \n   - Doval played a crucial role in the government\u2019s decision to abrogate Article 370, which granted special status to Jammu and Kashmir. His strategic planning ensured the smooth implementation of this constitutional change with minimal unrest.\n\n### 9. **Handling of China Border Crisis (2020\u20132021)**  \n   - During the military standoff with China in Ladakh, Doval was a key negotiator in talks with Chinese officials, showcasing his diplomatic skills in defusing tensions and ensuring India\u2019s strategic interests were protected.\n\n### 10. **Strengthening Intelligence and Security Framework**  \n   - As NSA, Doval has been instrumental in modernizing India\u2019s intelligence and security apparatus, fostering better coordination among agencies, and enhancing counter-terrorism capabilities.\n\n### 11. **Diplomatic Engagements and Strategic Alliances**  \n   - Doval has been actively involved in strengthening India\u2019s strategic partnerships, particularly with the US, Israel, and other nations, to bolster defense and intelligence cooperation.\n\nAjit Doval\u2019s contributions have earned him the nickname \u201cJames Bond of India\u201d and widespread respect for his ability to navigate complex security challenges with precision and foresight. His leadership continues to shape India\u2019s national security strategy in an increasingly volatile global environment.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
